Walked around china town and thankfully took a gamble on this whole in the wall. This shack is small with roughly 8 tables and a large window showing the different ducks and meat to the street walkers. We tried the BBQ pork along with noodles. The pork had a rich flavor which is hard to imitate at home. I forgot the name of the noodle we got but it was delicious. The broth was not overly salty yet had tons of taste. Service was above average. Price of lunch was dirt cheap. I would definitely recommend this to any china town visitors.  Try the BBQ pork CHEERS!!

Great Wall has been in Chinatown for so many years - I can remember going there since I was a kid, so that means at least 15 years at this point. The reason it's been around so long is because the food. There's always a reasonably long line for carryout since the BBQ is never dry and it's consistently flavorful. You get a ton of food for dishes that are usually under $7. Is the service lacking? Probably. But in my opinion, the food makes up for it.

They are enormous, tasty and if you think you need to order yourself more than one because of past experience with mini-egg rolls, stop!  Also, I am a big fan of their roast duck...tends to be my regular order:  - Egg roll - Roast duck - (and if someone is with me) Pork fried rice  You should at least show up for an order of egg rolls, I promise you won't be disappointed!

First of all, do not be put off by the ambiance and rather drab appearance of the place when you first walk in. One cannot judge a book by its cover because the food here is pretty good.  The meats are succulent, never dried out. The roasted meats have crispy skin and the steamed meats have delicious, juicy skin on the outside and tender meat on the inside. My personal favorites are the roasted duck and soy sauce steamed chicken. The portions are generous even for 2 people or one really hungry person.  Even though the service is nothing to be wowed over, and the place looks somewhat run down and dreary, the quality of the food here more than makes up for it. Plus, it's really good value for money with you consider their prices.  One thing to note though, is that credit cards are only accepted for orders above $10. Otherwise they'll tack on a service fee if you use your credit card so for small orders, it's best to have cash.
